      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DENNIS KEEPING (2) missed the frame last time at Dubbo but the start prior rocketed around 516m at Dubbo in 29.35. Has the ability and looks a key chance again. SIMPLY THE BEST (1) comes off an average effort last start when fifth at this track over 520m behind Tarawi Banjo (30.48) in a Grade 5. Placed at his previous run. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Likely to be about the money. HERA ROLEX (7) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 6 lengths at Gosford in a handy 29.42. Wide box to overcome but goes well at this distance. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Significant danger. WINSOME RAMBO (8) has strong credentials from this draw.",
